<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Transport">Transport</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Burundi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: Transport"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Transport_in_Burundi" title="Transport in Burundi">Transport in Burundi</a></div>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:BujumburaAirport.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/BujumburaAirport.jpg/220px-BujumburaAirport.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="165" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/BujumburaAirport.jpg/330px-BujumburaAirport.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/BujumburaAirport.jpg/440px-BujumburaAirport.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2272" data-file-height="1704" /></a><figcaption><a href="/wiki/Bujumbura_International_Airport" class="mw-redirect" title="Bujumbura International Airport">Bujumbura International Airport</a> terminal in Bujumbura</figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size mw-halign-left" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Truck_and_bicylists_near_Gitega,_Burundi.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img alt="two bicyclists hold on to back of truck descending a hill" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Truck_and_bicylists_near_Gitega%2C_Burundi.jpg/220px-Truck_and_bicylists_near_Gitega%2C_Burundi.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="117" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Truck_and_bicylists_near_Gitega%2C_Burundi.jpg/330px-Truck_and_bicylists_near_Gitega%2C_Burundi.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Truck_and_bicylists_near_Gitega%2C_Burundi.jpg/440px-Truck_and_bicylists_near_Gitega%2C_Burundi.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2162" data-file-height="1147" /></a><figcaption>Bicycles are a popular means of transport in Burundi</figcaption></figure>
<p>Burundi's transport network is limited and underdeveloped. According to a 2012 <i>DHL Global Connectedness Index</i>, Burundi is the least globalised of 140 surveyed countries.<sup id="cite_ref-134" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-134">&#91;130&#93;</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Bujumbura_International_Airport" class="mw-redirect" title="Bujumbura International Airport">Bujumbura International Airport</a> is the only airport with a paved runway and as of May 2017 it was serviced by four airlines (<a href="/wiki/Brussels_Airlines" title="Brussels Airlines">Brussels Airlines</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ethiopian_Airlines" title="Ethiopian Airlines">Ethiopian Airlines</a>, <a href="/wiki/Kenya_Airways" title="Kenya Airways">Kenya Airways</a> and <a href="/wiki/RwandAir" title="RwandAir">RwandAir</a>). <a href="/wiki/Kigali_International_Airport" title="Kigali International Airport">Kigali</a> is the city with the most daily flight connections to Bujumbura. The country has a road network but as of 2005<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Burundi&amp;action=edit">&#91;update&#93;</a></sup> less than 10% of the country's roads were paved and as of 2012<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Burundi&amp;action=edit">&#91;update&#93;</a></sup> private bus companies were the main operators of buses on the international route to Kigali; however, there were no bus connections to the other neighbouring countries (Tanzania and the Democratic Republic of Congo).<sup id="cite_ref-135" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-135">&#91;131&#93;</a></sup> Bujumbura is connected by a passenger and cargo ferry (the <a href="/wiki/MV_Mwongozo" title="MV Mwongozo">MV Mwongozo</a>) to <a href="/wiki/Kigoma" title="Kigoma">Kigoma</a> in Tanzania.<sup id="cite_ref-136" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-136">&#91;132&#93;</a></sup> There is a <a href="/wiki/East_African_Railway_Master_Plan" title="East African Railway Master Plan">long-term plan</a> to link the country via rail to Kigali and then onward to Kampala and Kenya.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Demographics">Demographics</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Burundi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Demographics"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
