<li><a href="/wiki/Patricia_Daley" title="Patricia Daley">Daley, Patricia</a> <i>Gender and Genocide in Burundi: The Search for Spaces of Peace in the Great Lakes Region</i></li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGatesAnthony_Appiah1999" class="citation book cs1">Gates, Henry Lewis; Anthony Appiah (1999). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/africanaencyclop00appi"><i>Africana: The Encyclopedia of the African and African American Experience</i></a>. New York, New York: Basic Civitas Books. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-465-00071-1" title="Special:BookSources/0-465-00071-1"><bdi>0-465-00071-1</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Africana%3A+The+Encyclopedia+of+the+African+and+African+American+Experience&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Basic+Civitas+Books&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.isbn=0-465-00071-1&amp;rft.aulast=Gates&amp;rft.aufirst=Henry+Lewis&amp;rft.au=Anthony+Appiah&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fafricanaencyclop00appi&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABurundi" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li>Ewusi, Kale and Akwanga, Ebenezer <i>Burundi's Negative Peace: The Shadow of a Broken Continent in the Era of Nepad</i></li>
<li>Jennings, Christian <i>Across the Red River: Rwanda, Burundi and the Heart of Darkness</i></li>
<li>Kayoya, Michel <i>My Father's Footsteps</i> (<i>Sur les traces de mon père</i>) East African Publishing House, 1973</li>
<li>Kayoya, Michel <i>Entre deux mondes</i> (Between two worlds) Lavigerie Éditeurs, Bujumbura: 1971. Kayoya was murdered during the 1972 genocide.</li>
<li>Kidder, Tracy, <i>Strength in What Remains</i> (A biography of a Burundian immigrant to the US)</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKruegerKathleen_Tobin_Krueger2007" class="citation book cs1">Krueger, Robert; Kathleen Tobin Krueger (2007). <i>From Bloodshed to Hope in Burundi: Our Embassy Years during Genocide</i>. Austin, Texas: University of Texas Press. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-292-71486-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-292-71486-1"><bdi>978-0-292-71486-1</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=From+Bloodshed+to+Hope+in+Burundi%3A+Our+Embassy+Years+during+Genocide&amp;rft.place=Austin%2C+Texas&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Texas+Press&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-292-71486-1&amp;rft.aulast=Krueger&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.au=Kathleen+Tobin+Krueger&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABurundi" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li>Melady, Thomas Patrick <i>Burundi: The Tragic Years</i></li>
<li>Nivonzima, David and Fendell, Len <i>Unlocking Horns: Forgiveness and Reconciliation in Burundi</i></li>
<li>Uvin, Peter <i>Life After Violence: A People's Story of Burundi</i></li>
<li>Watt, Nigel <i> Burundi: The Biography of a Small African Country</i></li>
